An sich macht es Spaß, auch wenn die Steuerung eine sehr steile Lernkurve hat. ABER das man in diesem Spiel KEINEN Spieler reporten kann, der im Ranked 4 Eigentore MIT Absicht macht, ist wirklich lächerlich. Ein wirklich wunderbarer Spielplatz für Trolle jeglicher Art. Wahnsinns Müll sowas! 
Natürlich gibt es auch immer mal wieder Ball-Bugs und die Server-Auswahl lässt mit hohem Ping doch manchmal zu wünschen übrig. 
@Devs: Fixt euer Game und gebt uns ein strenges Report-System!

Updated Review below:
The core gameplay concept is great on paper and depending how long it takes for the developers to release updates, it could become a milestone in competitive gaming in the future.

But right now, it has a ton of issues:
- Since the release date (June 19th, 2025) up to today (= 47 days later), only a single patch got released. This patch did not contain any real balancing changes and we are still waiting for the second update to the game.
Lots of issues persist with:
- netcode;
- ball physics; 
- abusable meta-game strategies;
- very "gamey" animation frame skip moves that suddenly change direction before you can react;
- a dumb priority system called "extra-effort" when fighting for ball control (especially in mid-air) that is comparable to an invisible stun/silence spell from RPGs. Meaning that whoever uses this mechanic in the right moment first, disables all other players around him from being able to access or hit the ball before they do. Other players can still move around and they don´t feel "stunlocked" because of it (thats the "invisible" part), but are basically excluded from getting the ball under their control for a short time. I would have loved to be around during the brainstorming session, when they came up with this mechanic and see how they justified implementing this idea;
- no promised cross-play with consoles;
- no replay feature to analyze games;
- no "report player" function;
- a completely obscure and intransparent matchmaking - system, where the game not only hides the "overall skill level" of your next match, but also hides the skill ranking of every single other player from you, so that it´s impossible for you to assess whether the matchmaking gods are teaming you up with complete noobs or the digitial equivalent of Lionel Messi. You cannot criticize what you don´t know, because the game does not tell you;
- no rematch button after losing a game against another team to play them again, even though the game is literally called "REMATCH"

Despite all this, the battle pass and microtransaction system is fully operational and at the same time completely unimpressive. 

"Yeah, we know it sucks to play goalkeeper and predict the enemy shot perfectly to catch it in mid-air, just for the ball to completely phase through your body like some kind of radio wave, going directly into your goal, but hey............can we maybe interest you into these dope-ass football sneakers on a Ronaldinho skin?"

Conclusion: I really like the game, i just hate it in it´s current form and the "service-part" of this live-service game is atrocious. I´ve had better service at a Mc Donald´s self-service checkout.

EDIT: The Game has been considerably improved in the last few weeks. Crossplay has now been included and several issues around netcode and ball physics have been adressed. There is still no replay viewer or a rematch button, but the game is a lot more stable and less unpredictable now. This is why i felt a need to change my review to a positive note now! This is only going to get better.

Game got worse after the latest patch. The devs barely seem to even work or try to properly communicate what their plans are. I could go into a lot of details but the main takeaways are:

- This feels like a glorified early access;
- Also has a battle pass (which takes too long to finish in my opinion);
- The core gameplay is cool, but it's full of glitches, weird priorities for the ball, etc;
- Netcode issues are present in a lot of matches, and you can end up getting randomly disconnected too;

NO! NO! NO! NO!

Abstain yourself from this game, Fifa is a god-tier game compared to this.

- Keeps disconnecting for no reason (no, my connection is fine, the game just decides to say "connection lost");
- Apparently there is drive, that isn't a bug (since it was always there), where people basically teleport/warp the ball and the ball keeps in their possession;
- Already encountered a cheater here, the ball just teleports and the cheater was scoring without giving us a chance to defend (here is a small clip of one of the occasions: https://imgur.com/BpX9dVl ) and no, the person wasn't lagging, since everytime he passed the ball, the passes were just fine;
- Another "fun" thing, is, sometimes you tackle and the game even tells you that you did (you gain points when you do so), but the oppoent just keeps the ball like nothing ever happened;
- And many many many other issues, glitches, bugs and etc;
- Honestly, just don't play this... you will NOT have fun. I was one of the people that enjoyed the Beta and now I utterly regret ever have bought a key for this, such a waste of money.

Ps.: With each update, the game becomes worse, they just keep updating the store.

Cheers, have fun.
